Prague Metro

The oldest section of Prague's metro is the red C line was started in 1966 and finally opened in 1974. It runs from Sokolovská 
(now called Florenc) to Kačerov. The length of this section in 6.6km and it contains 9 stations.



Glossary:

Section. A part of something (úsek, sekce).
Finally. You say finally when something took a long time (konečně).
Line. A railway line is a route from one place to another (trasa, linka).
